        "timestamp": "2020-03-19 23:27:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nNot sure if these are needed.  I'm concerned with over-configuration, where the installer gets confused with many pieces to configure.   Note that all these files can be overridden externally if they user wants different configuration directly in docker or helm charts, so it is possible to override the defaults.   Do you have in mind an specific use case scenario that you are concerned with?\n\nIn any case, they should be added to the installation files (base.conf) in drools-pdp, oom, (optionally docker repo and csit) for consistency and to track them.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
